Whether a copy of a spell is countered depends on how it was played - more specifically, whether it was cast or not. [autocard]Mirari[/autocard] or [autocard]Twincast[/autocard], for example, simply puts a copy on the stack. The chalice's ability will trigger when the original is cast, but not when it is copied (although note that if X = 2 then it will also be triggered by casting twincast/reverberate itself). [autocard]Isochron Scepter[/autocard] and [autocard]Panoptic Mirror[/autocard], although they also "make a copy" of a spell, actually cast that spell, so that will trigger the chalice.

How you cast a spell has no bearing on its converted mana cost, which will always be the same number for that spell. [autocard]Force of Will[/autocard]'s CMC will always be 5, even though no one will ever hardcast that.

